fields.value: Replication Data for: "Divided but United: Explaining Nested Public Support for European Integration" in West European Politics

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Replication data and syntax for the article Ejrnæs, A. & Jensen, M. D. Forthcoming. Divided but United: Explaining Nested Public Support for European Integration in West European Politics: https://doi.org/10.1080/01402382.2019.1577632

The data set comprises the following variables:

Variables 1-42: European Social Survey Cumulative File, ESS 1-7 (2016). Data file edition 1.0. NSD - Norwegian Centre for Research Data, Norway - Data Archive and distributor of ESS data for ESS ERIC.

Variables 43-341: Armingeon, Klaus, Christian Isler, Laura Kn€opfel, David Weisstanner, and Sarah Engler (2016). Comparative Political Data Set 1960–2014. Bern: Institute of Political Science, University of Bern.

Variables 342-343: Commission (2014). ‘EU Expenditure and Revenue 2000–2014’, available at: http://ec.europa.eu/budget/figures/interactive/index_en.cfm.

Variables 344-397: Teorell, Jan, Staffan Kumlin, Stefan Dahlberg, Sören Holmberg, Bo Rothstein, Natalia Alvarado Pachon & Richard Svensson (2017). The Quality of Government OECD Dataset. University of Gothenburg: The Quality of Government Institute, http://www.qog.pol.gu.se doi:10.18157/qogoecdjan19

Variables 398-458: Recodings

publicationCitation.value: Ejrnæs, A. & Jensen, M. D. 2019. Divided but United: Explaining Nested Public Support for European Integration in West European Politics: https://doi.org/10.1080/01402382.2019.1577632
